<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Charter<font size="4">ed By&nbsp;</font>The British Schools&nbsp;<font size="4">Founda<font size="4">t<font size="4">ion</font></font></font><br></i></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="1"><i><br></i></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" style=""><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: start;"><div style="margin: 0px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><font color="#000000" size="3"><br></font><span id="docs-internal-guid-e0bf5df0-9367-4cce-3110-7a0095475a50"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Please see below for an update;</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Recruitment and Retention</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Retention this year at the British School is nothing short of amazing. &nbsp;We estimate that retention of staff for next year is at 90%.  It will be great for our students and our school community to be able to work collaboratively again with familiar faces moving into next academic year 2018-2019.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Safeguarding training</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As designated safeguarding leads in our school, both Miss Ramskill and Mr Harvey will be attending Level 3, advanced training in Hong Kong. This will be the 2nd advanced training session for Miss Ramskill and Mr Harvey in the last 18 months which ensures BSY keeps up with the DfE expected guidance on safeguarding training.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Book Week - Monday 23rd - Friday 27th April</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Primary</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The first week back after Thingyan festival is our Whole School Book Week. In Primary, we will be looking at one book across the whole school. Our chosen book will be </span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">revealed to the children in our opening assembly on the 23rd of April. Throughout the week there will be lots of festivities such as a Book Fair by Peekaboo Books, a UK company who will be selling lots of fantastic titles over the course of two days.</span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> You can all look forward to, a 'Dress as a Character' Day, a Spelling Bee, 'Drop Everything and Read' and many more exciting events.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">EYFS</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">For Book Week, the Nursery and Reception children are invited to bring in a favourite book from home to share with their friends. We will also join in with the </span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">'Dress as a Character' Day on Friday 27th April, and so the Nursery and Reception children are invited to come into school dressed as one of their favourite story characters on this day. There will be a Costume Parade at 1:30pm on Friday 27th April on the Insein Campus playground, to which parents are invited to attend.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Secondary </span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We have lots of exciting things planned for World Book Week (April 23rd - 27th). Our main celebration will be on Tuesday 24th. Amongst other things, there will be a best-dressed competition for staff and students who will be dressing up as their favourite book characters; students will be off timetable and attending workshops of their choice; and we will be having short story readings from staff and students. A Secondary </span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Book Fair by Peekaboo Books will follow on May 10th and 11th.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Parent Survey</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The parent survey is now closed. &nbsp;We will be providing results in the summer term. 51% of the school community completed the survey.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Screen Time</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Please see this </span><a href="https://www.bps.org.uk/sites/beta.bps.org.uk/files/Policy%20-%20Files/Changing%20behaviour%20-%20children,%20adolescents,%20and%20screen%20use.pdf" style="text-decoration-line: none;"><span style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">link</span></a><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> to the British Psychological Society’s recent publication “Changing Behaviour: children, adolescents and screen use”.</span><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br class="kix-line-break"><br class="kix-line-break"></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Post-16 Curriculum Evaluation</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As part of completing the full picture of what curriculum secondary schools can offer at KS5 both Mr Gilberthorpe and Miss Ramskill are visiting two of our sister schools to explore options even further. &nbsp;They will be meeting with Principals and Heads of Secondary and staff at both The British School of Kuala Lumpur (A-Level programme) and Dover Court, Singapore (IBDP).</span></p><br><ul style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dover Court in Singapore (IBDP in action) - Tuesday 24th April 2018</span></p></li><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">BSKL in Malaysia (A Levels in action) - Thursday 26th April 2018</span></p></li><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Parent information session to confirm Post-16 curriculum to commence in August 2020 - Tuesday 22nd May 2018</span></p></li></ul><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Our New Campus</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We are delighted to inform our parents that the new campus is making very good progress and we are on course to move in for the start of Term 1 in August. We will be sending a more detailed update, including progress photographs, after the Easter vacation. Watch this space!</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;background-color:#ffffff;">&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Assessment Seminar</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">On Wednesday May 9th at 8.15am, Mr Harvey and Mr Gilberthorpe will be presenting information for parents on assessment in Primary and Secondary. &nbsp;This will focus primarily on how the school uses external assessments but will also provide valuable information on how to understand assessment in school. &nbsp;The workshop is open to parents from EYFS-Secondary and will be held in the assembly area, Insein Campus.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Parent Engagement Group</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Recently, myself and Mr Harvey met with a small group of BSY parents. &nbsp;The planning behind the meeting was to gauge/compile a list of thoughts and ideas towards how to further our communications between parents and the school. &nbsp;As we move into Term 3 (Summer term) we will be emailing all parents to come in to meet with us to discuss options towards further improving communications.  There will be a google doc provided for parents to complete. The date for this is Wednesday May 9th at 9.00am (after the assessment workshop).</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Health and Safety Drills</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As always, we continue to run various announced and unannounced safety drills in our campuses. &nbsp;The children have been excellent during these drills, demonstrating great maturity and independence. &nbsp;These drills will continue in Term 3. </span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Wishing you all a safe and relaxing Thingyan break.</span></p><br><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Regards,</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Adam Johnson</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Principal</span></p></span><font color="#000000" size="3"><br></font></font></div></span><div style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style=""><i style=""><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" style="" face="Arial, sans-serif"><b style="">World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: center;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font></div></div>]]></td>
